OL,3,COfsted to keep single-phrase ratings
OL,4,Cdespite calls to axe them
OL,6,FThe Department for Education (DfE) has
OL,7,Fsaid it will "continue to listen to
OL,8,Fviews and look at alternative
OL,9,Fsystems", but it believes there are
OL,10,F"significant benefits" to headline
OL,11,Fgrades awarded in England by the
OL,12,Fschools watchdog.
OL,14,FIn its response to an inquiry into
OL,15,FOfsted by the Commons Education Select
OL,16,FCommittee, the DfE said the overall
OL,17,Fjudgment provides a "succinct" summary
OL,18,Ffor parents and helps identify which
OL,19,Fschools need support.
