OL,3,COfsted to keep single-phrase ratings
OL,4,Cdespite calls to axe them
OL,6,FPaul Whiteman, general secretary of
OL,7,Fschool leaders' union the NAHT, said:
OL,8,F"Single-word judgments do not 'provide
OL,9,Fsignificant benefit' ` they are deeply
OL,10,Fharmful and must be scrapped entirely.
OL,12,F"Last year's tragic events showed
OL,13,Fthat, and we cannot rule out something
OL,14,Fawful happening again in future if the
OL,15,Finspectorate does not change.
OL,17,F"Should such a horrific situation
OL,18,Foccur, it will be ministers who need
OL,19,Fto answer for the decisions that have
OL,20,Fbeen taken."
OL,26,@pD@AOUtD@AOUyD@AOU|D@LO]
