OL,3,COfsted to keep single-phrase ratings
OL,4,Cdespite calls to axe them
OL,6,F"This is despite all the evidence that
OL,7,Fthese single-phrase judgments are the
OL,8,Fsource of sky-high stress and anxiety,
OL,9,Fdamaging the wellbeing of leaders and
OL,10,Fteachers, sapping morale and causing
OL,11,Fmany people to leave the profession.
OL,13,F"They stigmatise schools and colleges,
OL,14,Fmaking improvement more difficult to
OL,15,Fsecure, and thus they do a disservice
OL,16,Fto children, parents and communities.
OL,18,F"The problem is not presentational; it
OL,19,Fis that the system is fundamentally
OL,20,Fflawed and must change."
