OL,4,Cdespite calls to axe them
OL,6,FDaniel Kebede, general secretary of
OL,7,Fthe National Education Union (NEU),
OL,8,Fsaid the response misses an
OL,9,Fopportunity "to take significant steps
OL,10,Ftowards meaningful change".
OL,12,F"The DfE's refusal to accept that
OL,13,Fsingle-word judgments should be
OL,14,Fscrapped will be met with dismay
OL,15,Facross the teaching profession," he
OL,16,Fsaid.
OL,18,FLast month, Ofsted chief inspector Sir
OL,19,FMartyn Oliver launched the watchdog's
OL,20,FBig Listen public consultation which
OL,21,Fwill seek views about the inspectorate.
